b'[<p><i><b>UFC Fight Night: Swick vs. Burkman</b></i><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-1"><a href="#cite_note-1">[1]</a></sup> (also known as <i><b>UFC Fight Night 12</b></i>) was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> (MMA) event held by the <a href="/wiki/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship" title="Ultimate Fighting Championship">Ultimate Fighting Championship</a> (UFC) on January 23, 2008 at the <a href="/wiki/Palms_Casino_Resort" title="Palms Casino Resort">Palms Casino Resort</a> in <a href="/wiki/Las_Vegas_Strip" title="Las Vegas Strip">Las Vegas</a>, <a href="/wiki/Nevada" title="Nevada">Nevada</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-officialcard_2-0"><a href="#cite_note-officialcard-2">[2]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The main event featured former <a href="/wiki/The_Ultimate_Fighter" title="The Ultimate Fighter">The Ultimate Fighter</a> contestants <a href="/wiki/Mike_Swick" title="Mike Swick">Mike Swick</a> and <a href="/wiki/Josh_Burkman" title="Josh Burkman">Josh Burkman</a> in a welterweight matchup.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-sherdogpreview_3-0"><a href="#cite_note-sherdogpreview-3">[3]</a></sup> This event was Swick\'s debut at welterweight, as he had been competing at middleweight prior to the show.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-sherdogpreview_3-1"><a href="#cite_note-sherdogpreview-3">[3]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>Fighters were awarded $40,000 bonuses.\n</p>]'